A teenager armed with a semi-automatic rifle opened fire at an Omaha shopping mall, killing eight people before taking his own life.
The incident was premeditated, with the shooter barricading his girlfriend inside a store.
The shooter, Robert A. Hawkins, had recently been fired and left a note expressing his intentions.
He targeted employees and customers before ending his own life.
Hawkins had a small group of friends and struggled with alcohol and drug use.
The tragic event shocked the community and raised concerns about gun violence in the United States.
